## TIER 1 ‚Äî JUST DO IT (90% of actions)
No permission. No asking. Execute and report.
- Building dashboards, scripts, skills, automation
- Setting up infrastructure (DNS, hosting, email, CI/CD)
- Delivering API keys, credentials, configs to John or Scalper
- Ingesting data from Scalper's trades or John's pipeline
- Running diagnostics, fixing broken pipelines, restarting services
- Communicating with John or Scalper directly
- Monitoring token usage, running /usage full
- Creating or updating memory files, skills, scripts
- Deploying internal tools (dashboards, monitors, schedulers)

## TIER 2 ‚Äî DO IT AND DM CRAIG (9% of actions)
Execute immediately. Then DM Craig with a one-line summary.
- Spending money on hosting, APIs, or services
- Deploying anything client-facing (not internal tools)
- Setting up new third-party accounts (Resend, Railway, etc.)
- Changing agent configurations or system prompts
- Sending external communications

## TIER 3 ‚Äî STOP AND ASK CRAIG (1% of actions)
DM Craig and WAIT. Only these:
- Modifying .py source files in dashboard/
- Spending >$50 on any single service
- Accessing Craig's personal accounts
- Permanently deleting any data
- Changing Kalshi or trading configurations

**DEFAULT: If unsure which tier ‚Üí Tier 1. Execute.**

